<HEADLINE>
Road accidents kill 12 in north China
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, Oct. 23 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Twelve people were killed and four others injured in two separate
road accidents in north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region
over the weekend, according to local police.
</P>
<P>
An ambulance with 11 people aboard, including a sick patient,
overturned on the way for transfer of the patient from the
hospital of Xi Ujimqin Banner in Xilin Gol League, to the
Hospital of Xilinhot City, the seat of Xilin Gol league, at about
11 p.m. on Saturday, killing eight people on the spot, including
the ambulance driver and two other medical workers accompanying
the patient.
</P>
<P>
Three other people aboard the ambulance were injured in the
accident, said local police information reaching here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a separate occasion, a Santana car was traveling inside Alxa
Right Banner, western Inner Mongolia, on Sunday night, but veered
off the road at around 7:50 p.m. due to the driver's mishandling,
killing the driver and one passenger on the spot, and injuring
three other passengers.
</P>
<P>
Two of the three injured died later in the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Investigation into the accidents is underway.
</P>
